{"body": "> I don't think it is a good idea to flip this for all users in Rails 4 because albeit it is fantastic to push this stuff to find bugs, in practice that means bugs in production for end-users that are running multi-process anyway.\n\nThe amazing thing about this setting is that it's a default in a generator. If you're afraid of the multithreaded boogieman, you are free to turn it off. I agree that it does bring about the minimum amount of education that if you don't want to learn about thread safety in Ruby, you will need to find this setting and disable it.\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6259221", "created_at": "2012-06-11T23:34:25Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6685#issuecomment-6259221", "updated_at": "2012-06-11T23:42:43Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6685, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/tarcieri", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/4131d2f57a0db2a2b4d9a62bd389fd44?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fbeb22fb694d513edcf5533cf006dfeae.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/received_events", "gravatar_id": "4131d2f57a0db2a2b4d9a62bd389fd44", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "tarcieri", "type": "User", "id": 797, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52380552bd3543c15100c700"}, "id": 6259221, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6685"}
